info.headline: High Wind Warning issued April 19 at 6:27AM MDT until April 19 at 3:00PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM MDT THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...West winds 35 to 50 MPH with gusts up to 70 MPH expected. * WHERE...Central Laramie Range and eastern Platte County including Glendo, Wheatland, Chugwater, and the Bordeaux Interchange along Interstate 25. Southern Laramie Range and adjacent Foothills including Interstate 80 between Laramie and Cheyenne. * WHEN...Until 3 PM MDT today. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight or high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
